BBC.Rugby.Union.2014.11.15.Wales.v.Fiji.1080ip.h264-NX

BBC 1 HD 15th Nov 2014
2pm to 4:30pm Live

Gabby Logan is joined by studio guests Jonathan Davies, Jeremy Guscott and Nicky Little for live coverage from the Millennium Stadium as Wales face Fiji. Warren Gatland's Welsh side ran in nine unanswered tries when the sides last met at the 2011 World Cup, avenging a shock defeat at the previous tournament four years earlier. However, Wales struggled in the two most recent autumn internationals against the Pacific Islanders in Cardiff, being held to a draw in 2010 and only winning by a point in 2005. Eddie Butler, Philip Matthews and Martyn Williams provide the commentary.
